5925926\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p><strong>Helltides</strong> are one of the coolest endgame features in <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/diablo-4/40629\"><em>Diablo 4</em></a>, giving you a reason to explore the areas of <em>Diablo 4</em> you\u2019ve already visited many times before \u2014 such as <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/diablo-4-guides/23648271/altars-lilith-statues-locations-fractured-peaks\">The Fractured Peaks</a> or <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/diablo-4-guides/23739180/altars-lilith-statues-locations-scosglen\">Scosglen</a>. Even better, Helltides are an excellent source for loot, and y", "id": 1545289, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/diablo-4-guides/23755699/helltides-aberrant-cinders", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How Helltides work in Diablo 4 and how to spend Aberrant Cinders", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-19T12:31:02+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"Image: GSC Game World\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/stalker2-keyart-crop.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Xbox Game Pass is kicking off the holiday season a little early this year by adding <em><a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/game/stalker-2-heart-of-chernobyl/40777\">S.T.A.L.K.E.R. 2: Heart of Chornobyl</a></em> to its ever-expanding lineup on Nov. 20.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>S.T.A.L.K.E.R. 2</em> is the long-awaited sequel to 2007\u2019s <em>S.T.A.L.K.E.R.: Shadow of <em>Chornobyl</em></em>, which was a surprise hit from what was a largely under-the-radar Ukrainian studio called GSC Game World. The original game combined immersive first-person shooting with survival horror and roleplaying elements. Set against the backdrop of a sec", "id": 1545290, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/news/481397/stalker-2-xbox-game-pass-november-msfs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "S.T.A.L.K.E.R. 2 headlines big month for Xbox Game Pass", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-19T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/Screenshot-39.png?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,7.6801889768855,100,84.639635779482\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-drop-cap has-text-align-none\">If you\u2019re looking for dragons in The Sims, you\u2019ll have to look past the meager option in <em>The Sims 4</em> and head back into <em>The Sims 3</em>. Released in 2013, Dragon Valley adds a new fantasy world to the life simulation game. It\u2019s a medieval-inspired neighborhood with lore and legacy, where dragons abound. There have been dragons in most Sims games except <em>The Sims 2</em>, but <em>The Sims 3</em>\u2019s Dragon Valley world built off the myth of the creatures in a way that past and present games have not.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><a href=\"https://sims.fandom.com/wiki/Dragon_Valley\">Dragon Valley has a backstory<", "id": 1544851, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/opinion/479989/the-sims-3-dragon-valley-good-dragons", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Sims has a great history with dragons, but The Sims 4 doesn\u2019t do it justice", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-11-19T11:38:47+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"An image of a Chao in a modded Chao garden. The Chao is swimming in a pool of water.\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/11/chao-garden.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Fans <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/SonicTheHedgehog/comments/1dbd7ek/so_about_the_chao_on_the_cover_of_sonic_x_shadow/\">have lamented about the lack of Chao</a> in&nbsp;<em>Sonic x Shadow Generations</em>, but all is not lost. Thanks to the work of one modder, fans can raise their Chaos once again \u2014 and play a mod that adds an entirely new custom location to <em>Sonic Adventure 2</em>.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">The Chao, big-eyed creatures with tear-drop-shaped heads, are little pets you can take care of in the Sonic Adventure games. Fans of the original <em>Sonic Adventur", "id": 1544852, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/pc/481027/chao-garden-game-mod-sonic-adventure-2-battle", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/